<emphasis box="[783,898,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="432">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dorsal color pattern, with yellow stripes, and the globose pygophore distinguish this species from 
<emphasis box="[159,274,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="432">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1879" box="[159,270,1036,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">B. tricolor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
